## ACCESSIBILITY FOR TOUCH DEVICES

### 1. Font Size

**Standard:** 12-14px  
**Mobile:** 16px minimum for readability on small screens

```css
body {
  font-size: 16px;  /* Mobile */
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  body {
    font-size: 14px;  /* Tablet/Desktop */
  }
}

/* Larger text for better readability */
.text-lg {
  font-size: 18px;
}

.text-xl {
  font-size: 20px;
}
```

### 2. Color Contrast

**WCAG AA:** 4.5:1 for normal text  
**WCAG AAA:** 7:1 for normal text

```css
/* Good contrast */
.text-dark-on-light {
  color: #1F2937;  /* Dark gray on white */
  background: white;
  /* Contrast ratio: 17.5:1 */
}

/* Avoid low contrast */
.text-gray-on-gray {
  color: #999;  /* WRONG - hard to read */
  background: #f0f0f0;
}
```

### 3. Focus Indicators

**Important for keyboard navigation:**

```css
/* Visible focus indicator */
button:focus,
input:focus,
select:focus,
textarea:focus {
  outline: 3px solid #2180CE;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* High contrast for accessibility mode */
@media (prefers-contrast: more) {
  button:focus {
    outline-width: 4px;
    outline-color: #000;
  }
}
```

### 4. Reduced Motion

**Some users prefer minimal animations:**

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation: none !important;
    transition: none !important;
  }
}
```

---

## TESTING ON ANDROID

### 1. Chrome DevTools

```
1. Open DevTools (F12)
2. Click device toolbar icon (Ctrl+Shift+M)
3. Select "Android" device
4. Test responsive behavior
5. Check touch interactions
```

### 2. Android Emulator

```
1. Download Android Studio
2. Create virtual device
3. Run emulator
4. Open browser
5. Test full Android experience
```

### 3. Real Device Testing

```
1. Enable USB Debugging on Android device
2. Connect to computer
3. In Chrome: chrome://inspect
4. Click "inspect" to debug live
```

---

## PERFORMANCE METRICS

### Core Web Vitals

**Largest Contentful Paint (LCP):** < 2.5s  
**First Input Delay (FID):** < 100ms  
**Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS):** < 0.1

**Check with:**
```javascript
// Measure LCP
const observer = new PerformanceObserver((list) => {
  const entries = list.getEntries();
  const lastEntry = entries[entries.length - 1];
  console.log('LCP:', lastEntry.renderTime || lastEntry.loadTime);
});
observer.observe({ entryTypes: ['largest-contentful-paint'] });

// Measure FID
new PerformanceObserver((list) => {
  const entries = list.getEntries();
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    console.log('FID:', entry.processingDuration);
  });
}).observe({ entryTypes: ['first-input'] });
```

